But let's take a step back. "What's inside?" seems no one has asked yet.
At the top is an ESP32 camera board with a fisheye camera lens and a red infrared LED light taken from a Raspberry Pi camera.
That plastic box looks weird because the side panel of the nesting box can rotate. I bought it like this initially and couldn't change it, so I had to design it according to this situation.
Since there is no power supply in the garden, the entire device is powered by a solar panel and a 2600mAh 18650 lithium battery.
